							<div class="post">I thought the code was 14 characters because that&#039;s how many you were copying. For a 12-character code:<br /><br /><div class="codeheader">Code:</div><div class="code"><br />const int IDLEN = 12;<br />const int NAMELEN = 27;<br /><br />char currline[IDLEN + 1 + NAMELEN];&nbsp; // ID, plus comma, plus Name<br />char id[IDLEN+1];&nbsp; // ID plus a null terminator<br />char name[NAMELEN + 1]; // Name plus a null terminator<br /><br />while (sdin.getline(currline, sizeof currline, &#039;\n&#039;))<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; {<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; char *line = currline;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; int i;<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp;for (i=0; i &lt; IDLEN; i++)<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; id[i] = *line++;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;id[i] = &#039;\0&#039;;&nbsp; // Make it a valid string by adding a terminator.<br /><br />&nbsp; line++;&nbsp; // Skip the comma in the line<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <br />&nbsp; &nbsp;for (int 1=0; i &lt; NAMELEN; i++)<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; name[i] = *line++;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;name[i] = &#039;\0&#039;;&nbsp; // Make it a valid string by adding a terminator<br /></div>[/quote]</div>
