							<div class="post">So I finally got some time to get back into this project and I discovered an easy solution via trial and error.<br /><br /><div class="quoteheader"><a href="http://forum.arduino.cc/index.php?topic=60939.msg443052#msg443052">Quote from: PaulS on May 16, 2011, 07:07:35 am</a></div><div class="quote">That&#039;s a restriction of the underlying fat16 format - 8 characters for the file name, a dot, and 3 characters for the extension.<br /></div><br />No sorry, I meant the char name[28] array would not allow for more than 12 characters to be stored. It would cut off a name after 12.<br /><br />Anyhow, I figured out an easier way to code this section.<br /><br /><div class="codeheader">Code:</div><div class="code">char id [13]; //12 char plus null terminator<br />char name[50];<br /><br />while (sdin.getline(id, 12, &#039;,&#039;)){<br />&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;sdin.getline(name, 49, &#039;\n&#039;);<br />}<br /></div></div>
